"P2810140632" "You've found the reason for Flambeaux's attack.  This office is actually covertly home to the Paragon Caper, a tabloid that focuses mainly on super powered citizens.  This issue has some rather unflattering things to say about Flambeaux.  There's even some choice words for Blast Furnace, calling him a wishy-washy coward for turning his back on the people of Paragon City.  Maybe he's not here after Flambeaux after all."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - BlastFurnaceClue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue Name :
"P2536496192" "Blast Furnace's Explosives"
// DetailString :
"P1194099288" "'Oh, you want to know what I was doing?  Oh, err...well I was going after Flambeaux--like you--of course.  See these babies?  Just three of these will blow this place to smithereens.  Heh, and I know just where to put them, too."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Clue - FlambeauxClue 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P2556236538" "Flambeaux's completely lost it.  She was once a hero, but her desire for being the center of attention lead her down this path.  She's got to be dealt with.  It sounds as if Blast Furnace has stepped in to take her down, but is getting a bit careless.  You decide to step in and help him where he's left off."
// AcceptString :
"P1418351969" "Help Blast Furnace set up explosives to ensure no villains escape."
// SendOffString :
"P3149862930" "You were told that Blast Furnace was setting up explosives to allegedly destroy the building to make sure Flambeaux doesn't get out alive.  While that sounds sort of fishy, you think his idea isn't that far off the mark.  You head off to the office building to deal with Flambeaux."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P2155959504" "Make sure no one escapes"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P3974261617" "You're not sure what Blast Furnace is really doing there, but you ought to lend him a hand.  It will teach Flambeaux a lesson."
// TaskTitle :
"P3069943355" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Explosion in Peregrine</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color SlateGray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P668837280" "You can hear Flambeaux's high pitched voice screaming and whining off in the distance.  She's clearly still in here.  Good."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P1409944052" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Explosion in Peregrine</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color SlateGray><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You take the detonator from a startled Blast Furnace, press the switch and watch the building go up in flames.  Fortunately the building's workers made it out before you pressed the detonator, but you hope Flambeaux wasn't as lucky.  Blast Furnace and the citizens in the street stare in disbelief as you discard the detonator over your shoulder."
// Script Variable HOSTAGE_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P1145975293" "Punks!  I'm going to mess you up so bad your mama won't even recognize you."
// Script Variable HOSTAGE_ACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P833107387" "{HeroName}?  What are you doing here?"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P450128767" "Tank Smasher"
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P4044210824" "Nice bombs you got there.  You don't mind if I...YOINK!"
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P2840373652" "Let's kill these jerks and then blow this place to kingdom come!"
// Script Variable SayOnRescue :
"P2900817591" "Oh you're here for Flambeaux...oh.  Err, me too!"
// Script Variable SayOnRecapture :
"P2873266561" "Ugh, they've got me!"
