"P2266411271" "That poor Westin Phipps, I hope he gets well soon."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_Hero_SL8-9_Task_18 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - Maelstrom 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2373127615" "<color orange>Maelstrom stands before you with his hands raised away from his guns indicating that he wants to talk, not fight.</color><br><br>So, you managed to defeat that relic of a failed vision of hate and conquest.  I would have taken care of that obsolete trash myself if you hadn't showed up.<br><br>So why are you here, {HeroName}? I'm assuming it has something to do with these dangerous bomb triggers, am I right?"
// Answer Text :
"P1394888909" "Close.  I'm here to destroy them, and bring you in."
// Page InformationPage1 Text :
"P2628428287" "Bring me in?  For what?  Removing these deadly weapons from muderous fanatics? The last time I checked that's what a hero is supposed to do?  Or have things changed since I was last here?<br><br>What, did you bring a whole squadron of Longbow agents to come arrest the one guy who knows what these things are actually for?  I didn't realize the self-righteous enforcers of law and order needed to pack together like these sickening fascists in order to get anything done."
// Answer Text :
"P236951031" "I don't need to bring an army to stop people like you, Maelstrom."
// Page InformationPage2 Text :
"P148108377" "Hold your horses there a moment, rookie.  Are you telling me you came all the way here...intent on stopping the Fifth Column...intent on destroying these uranium filled remote bomb triggers...AND stopping me from performing whatever nefarious plan you've concocted in your head?  And you were going to do all of this by yourself?  What in the hell were you thinking!?"
// Answer Text :
"P1978139466" "That unlike you, I'm doing the right thing."
// Page InformationPage3 Text :
"P169857383" "<color orange>Maelstrom reaches for his guns at a blinding fast speed and points them right at your head.</color><br><br>Actually, you did the wrong thing, kiddo..."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P619489601" "If these bomb triggers were to get into the hands of the purchaser who commissioned them, or anyone else for that matter, the sheer amount of destruction that could be caused is unfathomable.  Whatever plan these trigger switches are intended for can be stopped by destroying the trigger switches themselves.  You may be able to track down who the buyer is later, but you have to put a stop to the means by which their plan is intended to be carried out before any innocent lives are lost!"
// AcceptString :
"P697914830" "Destroy the cache of bomb triggers!"
// SendOffString :
"P3796081829" "From the additional information contained within the report, you're able to figure out where the Fifth Column sleeper cell was originally located.  Even though the report claims it was later abandoned, it's quite likely the the facists have returned to their old haunts.  Track them down, destroy those triggers at all costs, then see if you can find out anything about who the buyer is."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P2194928730" "Destroy the Bomb Triggers!"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P2127695573" "You still need to find the old Fifth Column base and destroy those triggers!"
// TaskTitle :
"P864912609" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>An Unstable Trigger</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color Deepskyblue><i>Hero Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P1643283093" "It definitely looks like the Fifth Column has restarted their base.  And that means you'll find those triggers here.  Destroy them at once before any can slip into the hands of the mysterious buyer."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P2992293330" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>An Unstable Trigger</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color Deepskyblue><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You not only managed to destroy all of the bomb triggers, but also stopped the Oberst leading the manufacturing operations.  Although Maelstrom may have gotten away, you still managed to foil his plans for whatever insidious design he had intended for those bomb triggers."
// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// - ScriptDef - TimedObjective 
// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable ObjectiveUIText :
"P2014079314" "Talk to Maelstrom"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P2231737336" "Raserei Ubermenschen Oberst Gottliener"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYINFO :
"P1563950234" "The Raserei Ubermenschen Obersts make up the inner circle that surrounds the 5th Column leadership. They are charged with the grand stratagems that further the ultimate goal of the 5th Column: the eventual domination of the world. The leaders of the Column foster a competitiveness between these high ranking officers in order to prevent any single one of them from acquiring too much power and becoming a threat."
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P3626873645" "MAELSTROM!!!  You will not get away with this doublecross!"
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P949480854" "{HeroName}!?  So this is what his plan was the whole time? To set us up on behalf of you foolish heroes?"
// Script Variable BOSS_1STBLOOD_DIALOG :
"P3547726888" "No...I think you have been fooled by Maelstrom the same way in which he tricked us.<em t=3>He only planned on stealing our triggers, never buying them!"
// Script Variable BOSS_75HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P3023094675" "Don't you find the bitter humor in all of this?<em t=3>While you're fighting us, he is running off with all of our bomb triggers!"
// Script Variable BOSS_50HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P1978745693" "No?  You don't find that funny?<em t=3>NOR DO I!  And once I defeat you, I will crush that doublecrossing rat beneath my boot!"
// Script Variable BOSS_25HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P2244345712" "I can hear him laughing down the halls even now!<em t=3>I will find you and destroy you Maelstrom!"
// Script Variable BOSS_DEAD_DIALOG :
"P3845855885" "No!  It does not end this way..."
// Script Variable BOSS_KILLEDHERO_DIALOG :
"P352013893" "You are nothing more than a pathetic cur."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptOberstDefeated 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P3698223304" "Find and defeat the 5th Column Oberst!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - Objective 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P2236247783" "You have defeated the Oberst in charge of this sleeper cell."
// Script Variable PET_NAME :
"P1197252391" "Maelstrom"
// Script Variable PET_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P1584488575" "{HeroName}?  Wasn't expecting that one."
// Script Variable PET_ACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P3203293443" "Who's side are you on, eh?"
// Script Variable RescueObjectiveText :
"P492362814" "Find Maelstrom"
// Script Variable BOSS_DISPLAYNAME :
"P2188119240" " Vampyr Commandant"
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P4073844410" "You vill be going novhere, Maelstrom!  Once I find you, you vill DIE!"
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P489202874" "And you too, cretin.  You BOTH shall die!  Starting vith you...<em t=3>...and zen I go find Maelstrom!"
// Script Variable SayOnBetrayal :
"P2139499375" "You just gave me the intel on your mission and troop size.  Bad, bad move...<em t=3>Too bad you won't live to learn from your mistake, soldier."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptMaelstromCaptured 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable OBJECT_DISPLAYNAME :
"P3894283507" "Uranium Bomb Trigger Shipment Container"
// Script Variable ACTOR_GUARDING_DIALOG :
"P2469182156" "Only the Oberst can grant authorization to move the triggers."
// Script Variable ACTOR_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P3991869359" "Wait...You're not the Oberst!  We're being betrayed!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Objective - ScriptTriggersDestroyed 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Description :
"P3070513838" "Destroy the Container Holding the Bomb Triggers!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - Objective 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P555863662" "You have prevented Lord Caernoz from returning through the portal... For now."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - TaskSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog :
"P3190781600" "You've destroyed the container holding all of the uranium-filled bomb triggers.  Longbow can return to mop up any of the Fifth Column stragglers left in the base."

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Reward - ReturnSuccess 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// RandomFameString :
"P2724101746" "Hey, isn't that {HeroName}?  The same {HeroName} who faced off against Maelstrom and sent him packing?  Right on!"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task - AM_Vig_SL8-9_Task_18 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - Maelstrom 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2188624221" "Look... We both don't like the Fifth Column, right? So I'm here to drain them of their resources.  Uranium, specifically.  Now, you can go ahead and act the hero and stop me, but you're only hurting yourself.  With my help, we can both team up and put a stop to them together.<br><br>And if I'm reading your eyes right, you might be interested in getting your hands on what I'm here for.  After all, there's more than enough to share."
// Answer Text :
"P1057136883" "I'm listening, Maelstrom."
// Page MaelTradeOne Text :
"P828430251" "That's what I thought.  Getting tired of all the speeches about doing things for others, aren't you?  While you're busting your rear-end saving all those lives, you're watching all the fatcats living the high life, am I right?<br><br><color orange>Maelstrom studies you for a moment.</color><br><br>So let's make a deal, you and I."
// Answer Text :
"P2596627009" "What do you have in mind?"
// Page MaelTradeTwo Text :
"P1884018981" "I'm here to pick up two containers of remote detonation trigger switches for specially made bombs that are in the possession of my employer.  Now...I can grab one container, and you can grab the other.  Once we have both of them, we'll meet up and that's when I'll introduce you to the people I work for.  I think you might find their point of view is a little more in line with yours."
// Answer Text :
"P3784427279" "What'll stop me from just running off with my container?"
// Page MaelTradeThree Text :
"P1264876040" "If you do that, not only will you not get to meet my friends, but I'll also put a bullet through your eyes.  I'd think that should be incentive enough, wouldn't you say?  So what's your choice soldier?<br><br><color orange>Maelstrom extends his hand.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P1067784239" "I'm in.  I want to meet your friends."
// Page MaelTradeFour Text :
"P1286656954" "<color orange>You and Maelstrom shake hands.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P3189142790" "[Close]"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Task Header Items 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// IntroString :
"P1888433143" "Even if you were able to destroy the triggers, what's to stop the mysterious buyer from contracting someone else to create a similar form of weapon?  If you really want to put an end to this problem, you need to go straight to the head of the problem - and decapiate it.  Sure, it's a bit extreme in its approach, but so are countless lives being snuffed out needlessly.  You need to find the buyer who commisioned the Fifth Column and take that ONE person out if you really want to save MANY lives."
// AcceptString :
"P537156707" "Assassinate the buyer of the bomb triggers!"
// SendOffString :
"P2190303003" "From the additional information contained within the report, you're able to figure out where the Fifth Column sleeper cell was originally located.  Even though the report claims it was later abandoned, it's quite likely that the facists have returned to their old haunts.  Find the base, assassinate the buyer when they're at their most vulnerable, and destroy any of the remaining bomb caches that are still there."
// ActiveTaskString :
"P3723686353" "Assassinate the Bomb Trigger Purchaser!"
// YoureStillBusyString :
"P1201717962" "You still need to find the old Fifth Column base and assassinate the person intending to buy the bomb triggers!"
// TaskTitle :
"P2564503433" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>An Unstable Trigger</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color SlateGray><i>Vigilante Mission</i></color></span>"

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// MissionDef 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// EntryString :
"P1436474175" "It definitely looks like the Fifth Column has restarted their base. With luck, you'll be able to find buyer here.  You might consider tricking them into lowering their guard.  Who knows what kind of protection they're guarded by."
// ExitStringSuccess :
"P3071487261" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>An Unstable Trigger</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color SlateGray><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>In an attempt to get to the top of the chain of command behind the manufacture of these bomb triggers, Maelstrom managed to get away.<br><br>However, you were still able to destroy the bomb triggers.  And even better, you managed to infuriate Maelstrom.<br><br>The next time you meet him, hopefully that anger will cause him to make a fatal mistake."
// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// - ScriptDef - TimedObjective 
// ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Script Variable BOSS_INACTIVE_DIALOG :
"P3456280935" "You can't hide forever, Gottliener.  Accept the facts...I betrayed you.<em t=3>NOW HAND OVER THOSE TRIGGERS!"
// Script Variable BOSS_ATTACK_DIALOG :
"P591449011" "{HeroName}. You weren't part of the briefing...<em t=3>But I'm not dumb enough to think even someone like you is working for the Fifth Column."
// Script Variable BOSS_1STBLOOD_DIALOG :
"P2251188525" "Nor am I dumb enough to think you're here to help me, either."
// Script Variable BOSS_75HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P2523601660" "What's your mission, {HeroName}? Stopping the Column?"
// Script Variable BOSS_50HEALTH_DIALOG :
"P4165389218" "Intel on you is sketchy at best.  What's your mission, soldier?"
// Script Variable BOSS_KILLEDHERO_DIALOG :
"P358394095" "Pathetic.  What are heroes made out these days?"
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P3475866188" "Enough! The enemy of my enemy is my friend.<em t=3>So before you go any further, let's see if we can work together."
// Script Variable SaysList :
"P1405532461" "You get the container just up ahead and I'll meet you in the back"

